# Onshape via Playwright

The Onshape 3D model is a **WebGL canvas — not in the DOM**; only the feature
tree, dialogs, and parameter inputs are. Combined with Angular-generated class
names (no `data-test`/aria contract), UI selectors are brittle. So: use Playwright
for **auth, navigation, UI-only edits, and visual verification**; do the geometric
edit through @onshape/api.

## Auth — the storageState pattern

Onshape uses cookie-based sessions and can enforce 2FA, which blocks scripted
headless login (plus bot detection flags `navigator.webdriver`/TLS fingerprint).
Don't script the password — capture the session once, interactively, and reuse it:

```bash
# headed, one time: solve password + 2FA + "remember this device for 30 days"
npx playwright codegen --save-storage=auth.json https://cad.onshape.com/signin
```

Then every headless run starts logged in:

```ts
const context = await browser.newContext({ storageState: 'auth.json' });
```

Refresh `auth.json` when the session expires. For unattended runs prefer API keys
(@onshape/api) — they never hit a session timer or a 2FA wall.

## Editing a feature

Double-click a feature in the tree → its dialog opens → fill the input → confirm
with the **green check** (or `Enter`); red `X` / `Escape` cancels. Accepting
**auto-commits to the workspace** — there is no per-edit Save button; Versions are
manual snapshots. The depth/distance input takes an expression string like `50 mm`.

```ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
test.use({ storageState: 'auth.json' });

test('edit extrude depth', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto(DOC_URL);                                  // …/documents/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}
  const row = page.getByText('Extrude 1', { exact: true });  // GUESS — wait on DOM, canvas is WebGL
  await expect(row).toBeVisible({ timeout: 30_000 });
  await row.dblclick();                                       // GUESS — fallback: right-click -> Edit
  const depth = page.getByRole('textbox', { name: /depth|distance/i }); // GUESS
  await depth.fill('50 mm');
  await page.keyboard.press('Enter');                        // accepts + auto-commits
  await row.dblclick();
  await expect(depth).toHaveValue(/50\s*mm/i);               // verify persisted
});
```

> **Every editor selector above is an unverified guess.** Regenerate against a
> live document with `playwright codegen` before relying on them. Spec API:
> @playwright/api · runner: @playwright/cli · recording: @playwright/codegen.

## WSL

`npx playwright install chromium` (the `--with-deps` variant needs sudo; the
binary alone runs headless). A runnable example with a creds-free headless proof
of the dialog mechanics is in `examples/onshape/` (`npm run test:mock`).
